  <description><![CDATA[<p>Clarion Hotel Bergen is in an enviable, harbour front location at Bryggen wharf, which is one of Norway’s seven UNESCO World Heritage sites. The hotel’s historic wharf building was formerly the F Beyer factory building, and is located where <a data-udi="umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5}" title="Bergen">Bergen’s</a> main sights of the harbour, fish market and Fløibanen Funicular are only a few steps away.</p>
<p>This classic hotel offers great facilities which are complimented by the spacious and comfortable rooms, many with views over the harbour. There is a generous hot and cold buffet breakfast included to get you ready for a day of exploring this vibrant city and tea and coffee is available all day from the lobby. Guests residing in the hotel also receive free WiFi plus access to the fitness room and sauna.</p>]]></description>
